<HEADLINE> Some 2,500 Somali Refugees Return Home from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 2,500 Somali refugees
sheltered at the Teferi Ber refugee camp in eastern Ethiopia have
returned home recently, Ethiopia's Refugees and Returnees
Affairs Administration said today.
</P>
<P>
The returnees, who had lived in Ethiopia for the past six years,
are the first batch of refugees who agreed to voluntary return
after a fact finding team confirmed the prevalence of peace in
northern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) has
provided each returnee with plastic shelter, night clothings, food
grains, utensils and the transportation fare.
</P>
<P>
More than 287,000 Somali refugees are sheltered in nine camps
in the Somali Regional State of Ethiopia. enditem

