<HEADLINE> Norway Provides Grant to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Norwegian government will this
year make available to Zimbabwe a 20 million US Dollar grant to
support development efforts in the sectors of health, economic
projects, human rights and technical assistance.
</P>
<P>
An agreement signed here today between the two governments will
enable this southern African country to tap into a three year
program of assistance under which Norway plans to give 53 million
US Dollars in grants.
</P>
<P>
''I note with appredciation that all your assistance is in grant
form which helps us to minimise our indebtedness thereby release more
resources for the development of our country,'' said senior Finance
Secretary Charles Kuwaza who signed on behalf of Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian Ambassador to Zimbabwe Johan Dahl signed on behalf of
his country. enditem


