<HEADLINE> (urgent) Yeltsin and Kohl Say NATO Charter to be </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl and
Russian President Boris Yeltsin said today that the charter
defining a new security partnership between NATO and Russia would
be signed next month.
</P>
<P>
"On May 27 the treaty will be signed in Paris -- this means we
must hurry," Yeltsin told a press conference after talks with Kohl
in the Black Forest spa town Baden-Baden.
</P>
<P>
The charter aims to mollify Moscow over the eastwards expansion
of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO). "Some 90 percent
of the charter is completed," Kohl said, adding that he was
"confident" that the charter could be completed by the May 27
deadline.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 10 percent comprised the most difficult aspect of
negotiations, according to Kohl.  
</P>
