<HEADLINE> S. African Suggested to Fluoridate Drinking Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The South African Health
Department has recommended to start immediately to fluoridate all
South Africans' drinking water.
</P>
<P>
This program should begin in the major metropolitan areas, the
department said in its white paper on transformation of health
system released today.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, alternative methods of fluoridation
such as fluoride toothpaste and mouth rinses should be introduced
in schools.
</P>
<P>
Legislation should be drawn up to enable fluoridation of milk
and salt. In addition, a nutrition program should also be
introduced to remove or reduce the levels of sugar in infant and
baby foods.
</P>
<P>
It should also aim to reduce the level of added sugars in
common foods and encourage manufacture and use of sugar-free
foods, snacks and drinks.
</P>
<P>
Food labels should carry accurate information on sugar
content, the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
