<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government today told
West embassies to Kenya to respect diplomatic protocol and raise
their concerns with the government instead of going public with
them.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held here today, Kenyan Foreign Minister
Kalonzo Musyoka said that his government was gravely concerned
West embassies were returning to the confrontational style of
former U.S. Ambassador Smith Hempstone before Kenya's first
multi-party elections in 1992.
</P>
<P>
A joint statement signed on Wednesday by 14 West embassies
deplored recent actions by Kenyan police and called for free
speech and assembly in the election year.
</P>
