<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Retreat Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip shares retreated
slightly today, ending a week-long rally that had recovered nearly
300 points of the 700-point slide by the Dow Jones industrial
average over the past month.
</P>
<P>
The Dow was down 21.27 points to 6,658.60.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a narrow margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume reaching 502.81
million shares as against 498.82 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Other major indicators were mixed. The struggling Nasdaq market
posted the biggest gains with the recovering of some depressed
technology shares.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 1.76 to 761.77, and
the NYSE's composite index fell 1.10 to 400.65.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 6.79 to 1,217.06, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 0.99 to 555.52.
</P>
<P>
As bond prices rose today, the yield on the 30-year Treasury
bond fell as low as 7.03 percent, down from late Wednesday's 7.09
percent, before settling at 7.06 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
