<HEADLINE> Aviation Administration Chongqing Bureau Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, China's newest
municipality as of last March, opened its own regional aviation
administration bureau today.
</P>
<P>
China Civil Aviation Administration Chongqing Bureau was set up
to replace the China Civil Aviation Administration Sichuan
Provincial Bureau, with approval from the Civil Aviation
Administration of China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Bureau is set up to meet changes in the management
system since Chongqing become China's fourth municipality directly
under the central government.
</P>
<P>
The bureau, affiliated with Southwest China Civil Aviation
Administration, is in charge of management of Jiangbei Airport of
Chongqing. Three other airports of Xichang, Nanchong, and Daxian,
which used to be under the supervision of the China Civil Aviation
Administration Sichuan, will have the Southwest China Civil
Aviation Administration as the new authority.
</P>
<P>
Jiangbei Airport, a class I airport authorized to receive
foreign airplanes, is one of the ten largest airports in China. It
handled 2.47 million passengers and 45,000 tons of mail last
year. Jiangbei connects Chongqing with 48 other cities across the
country by offering 550 flights each week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
