<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Egyptian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) Li Ruihuan told Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal
Ahmed El-Ganzouri here today that his visit to China will
vigorously push ahead the development of friendly cooperative
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the two countries have always enjoyed a good
relationship. Both China and Egypt are developing countries with a
long history of civilization. Both are faced with the challenges
of economic development and improvement of people's living
standards, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries hold identical or similar views
on many international issues. He expressed gratitude to
El-Ganzouri for Egypt's support to China on a number of crucial
issues, especially at the last session of the Human Rights
Commission of the United Nation that was held in Geneva this week.
</P>
<P>
El-Ganzouri said that the two countries have had similar
experiences in the past and maintained close relations through all
times. He said that the Egyptian people deeply feel that the
Chinese people are their sincere friend. Egypt will never forget
that China supported and helped it during hard times, he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the Sino-Egyptian relationship is an excellent
example of bilateral relations in the world.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the development of a long-term, steady and
friendly relationship of cooperation between the two countries is
not only in the interests of the two peoples, but also conducive
to the peace and stability of their own regions and the world as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
He said that contacts between the CPPCC and the Advisory
Council of Egypt have grown in the past few years. The enhancement
of exchanges between them will benefit the development of
bilateral relations and the improvement of the understanding
between the two peoples. Li said he hoped that the two sides will
continue their exchanges and cooperations at all levels and
further advance the existing friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
On the human rights issue, Li said that China respects the
norms of human rights acknowledged by the international community
and actively participates in human rights activities in the
international arena.
</P>
<P>
However, it believes that some specific human rights norms
should conform to the specific conditions in different countries,
otherwise these norms will become empty talks, he said.
</P>
<P>
China also holds that human rights find expression in the
course of history, which all countries are in, he said. Since the
conditions of different countries vary from one another, it is
natural that they have differences on the human rights
issue. China is firmly opposed to the practice of interfering in
other countries' internal affairs under the pretext of human
rights.
</P>
<P>
El-Ganzouri said that Egypt has made remarkable achievements in
its economic development, though it still has room to
improve. Egypt wishes to conduct fruitful cooperation with China,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China is delighted to see the improvement of
people's living standards in Egypt under the leadership of
President Muhammed Hosni Mubarak. He wished Egypt greater success
in its development. The two countries should learn from each other
in their economic development, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
