<HEADLINE> China Sets up 36 Local Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Guiyang City Cooperative Bank,
the first local bank in China's southwestern Guizhou province,
opened business here today.
</P>
<P>
China has set up 36 local banks throughout the country, all of
which have been approved by the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
The Guiyang City Cooperative Bank is a joint-stock bank, with a
capital of 200 million yuan which have been pooled by local
enterprises, residents, and the government.
</P>
<P>
"Setting up local banks in the form of city cooperative banks
is an important measure of deepening reform of the country's
financial structure," an official from the People's Bank of China
said.
</P>
<P>
China set up its first local bank in the boom-town of Shenzhen
in 1995. 
