<HEADLINE> Thailand Imports 1,444 Autos in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Thailand imported 1,444
completely built-up vehicles in March this year, mostly from
Europe, according to the Thai Customs Authorities.
</P>
<P>
Among the imported vehicles, some 1,100 were shipped from
Europe, including 326 Volks Wagens, 269 Volvos, 201 Mercedes
Benzes, 116 Nissans, 81 Cherokees, and 31 Audis, said the Customs
Department under the Finance Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Imports in the month from Japan totaled 297, including 241
Toyotas, 37 Suzukis, and 10 Mazdas, the department said.
</P>
<P>
Only 47 autos, all Chryslers, were imported from the United
States, it added.
</P>
<P>
The department said that it collected 829.9 million baht (33.2
million US dollars) in import duties, or an average of 547,771
