<HEADLINE> China-Egypt Memorandum of Understanding Signed in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A memorandum of understanding
between China and Egypt was signed here today by Chinese Premier
Li Peng and visiting Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal Ahmed
El-Ganzouri.
</P>
<P>
According to the memorandum, China will provide experience on
special economic zones, work with Egypt on a feasibility study of
free zone projects, and encourage Chinese businessmen to take part
in projects at the North Suez Gulf Free Zone.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum will be beneficial to both countries and
increase exchanges of their successful experience in economic
reform.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the signing ceremony, Premier Li met with Egyptian
entrepreneurs, accompanying Prime Minister El-Ganzouri on his
China trip. 
</P>
