<HEADLINE> Muslims Gather for Corban Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 Muslims from 10
ethnic minorities gathered in Beijing this afternoon to celebrate
the annual Corban festival, one of the three major Mohammedan
festivals.
</P>
<P>
Vice-presidents of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress Chen Siyuan and Temur Dawamad, State Councillor
and minister in charge of the State Nationalities Affairs
Commission Ismail Amat, and Vice-chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference Seypidin Azizi were present at today's gathering.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from China's 10 Muslim ethnic groups including
Hui, Uygur, Kazak, Uzbek, Tajik, Kirgiz, Tartar, Bao'an, Sala,
and Dongxiang attended the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the get-together, Ismail Amat extended his festival
greetings to 17 million Muslims in China.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese Muslims along with China's other ethnic groups
have made great contributions to the unification and prosperity of
the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
"All ethnic groups will have their dignity and status as long
as they stay in the big family of the motherland; all ethnic
groups will enjoy genuine equality, unity, mutual help, and
religious freedom as long as they live under the socialist
system," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Socialism will eventually lead to common prosperity for all
ethnic groups," he said.
</P>
<P>
Teachers and students from the music and dance departments of
the Central University of Nationalities performed at the
gathering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
