<HEADLINE> Ashrawi: Settlement A Bomb Shell Against Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Hanan Ashrawi, Minister of Higher
Education in the Palestinian National Authority, has warned that
settlement in Arab East Jerusalem is a bomb shell against the
peace process.
</P>
<P>
In an interview printed in today's Bahraini newspaper "Akhbar
Al Khaleej", Ashrawi accused Israel of non-commitment to the
principles of the peace process and imposing a fait accompli on
the Palestinian people.
</P>
<P>
She asserted that violence was not coming from nowhere, and the
Palestinian side had warned the U.S. Administration against a new
wave of violence as a consequence of Israel's hardline policies.
</P>
<P>
She underscored that the U.S. use of veto power in the
U.N. Security Council meant that the Palestinians could not resort
to any thing other than violence.
</P>
<P>
Ashrawi noted that there have been encouraging signs in the
Arab world ever since the convocation of the recent Arab foreign
ministers meeting in Cairo, but there ought to be a united Arab
strategy and strong political support for the Palestinian cause.
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem was not a mere Palestinian issue, but an
Arab-Islamic-Christian one, she stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian Minister appealed to the Arabs to use their
potential force, pointing out that "the present stage was the most
difficult one we and the Arab nation are experiencing." 
</P>
