<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Meets Latin American Parliament President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here this
afternoon with visiting Juan Adolfo Singer, president of the Latin
American Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders expressed the hope for continuous growth of
friendly ties between the NPC and the Latin American Parliament by
concerted efforts.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi said China's NPC has maintained close contacts and
good cooperation relations with most member states of the Latin
American Parliament. Such relationships have been enhanced over
the past few years, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said: "I have visited Argentina, Brazil, and Cuba. When
the 96th Inter-parliamentary Conference was held in Beijing last
September, I had the opportunity to exchange views with leading
members of delegations from the parliaments of the Latin American
countries."
</P>
<P>
Qiao said the contact between the NPC and parliaments of the
Latin American countries and the Latin American Parliament has
increased their mutual understanding, trust, and friendship and
promoted their mutually beneficial cooperation in every field.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that with concerted efforts, such
exchanges and cooperation will be enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China is now concentrating on its modernization
drive so as to eliminate its backwardness.
</P>
<P>
But, he said, to thoroughly change backwardness requires
efforts by several generations.
</P>
<P>
Singer said China constitutes an important factor for
safeguarding stability in the world and its status in the
world today has been becoming increasingly important.
</P>
<P>
"It is our priority objective to develop our ties with
China. We are willing to establish a long-term and friendly
cooperative mechanism with China's NPC," he said.
</P>
<P>
Singer noted China's great progress and its efforts to
eliminate poverty. Latin America is also confronted with issues
similar to China.
</P>
<P>
The Latin American countries are far from China, but their
cooperation has been becoming increasingly closer. Their relations
should be developed further in the political, economic, and
cultural aspects, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi's wife Yu Wen attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Singer and his party arrived here on April 16 at the invitation
of the NPC Standing Committee. 
</P>
