<HEADLINE> Chinese President on Sino-Russian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
expressing satisfaction with the healthy development of
Sino-Russian ties and relations between the two armed forces, said
today that he is confident about the future of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
No matter how the world changes, China will not turn away from
its policy of "good-neighborliness, equality and mutual trust,
mutual-beneficial co-operation, and common development" towards
Russia, Jiang told visiting Russian Defence Minister Igor
Nikolayevich Rodionov this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In welcoming his Russian guests, Jiang said that Rodionov's
visit will promote friendly co-operation between the two countries
and the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to Sino-Russian ties and there
are many prospects and great potential for co-operation in various
fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
To establish a kind of strategic co-operative partnership for
the 21st century, based on equality and mutual trust between the
two nations, is the basic interest of the two peoples, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
It is also significant for safeguarding peace and stability of
the Asia-Pacific region and the world, and for establishing a just
and rational new world order of politics and economy, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang asked Rodionov to convey his regards to President Yeltsin
and Prime Minister Chernomyrdin and Rodionov also conveyed
President Yeltsin's regards to Jiang, saying the Russian President
is looking forward to Jiang's coming visit.
</P>
<P>
The Defence Minister expressed his satisfaction with his
current visit and pleasure with China's great achievements in its
reform and opening up drive.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two sides have discussed international and
regional issues and reached a consensus.
</P>
<P>
The people of the two countries are close friends and the two
countries are dedicated to establishing a strategic co-operative
partnership for the 21st century based on equality and mutual
trust, he said.
</P>
<P>
Russia will continue to promote mutually beneficial
co-operation to contribute to safeguarding peace and stability of
the Asia-Pacific region and the world, he said. 
</P>
