<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Alerts Army to Conspiracies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani today called on the armed forces to be on alert
against "international conspiracies."
</P>
<P>
Marking the Army day here, he said that the military should
maintain their combat readiness in light of "many conspiracies
by the international camp of unbelievers against the country."
</P>
<P>
He cited the Berlin court ruling that the Iranian leadership
was behind the 1992 killings of Kurdish dissidents as a joint
conspiracy by the United States, Israel and the German judiciary
against the Islamic republic.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not pointed his finger directly at the German
government today in his statement.
</P>
<P>
He said the foreign enemies of Iran had considered at least
three devices for crippling the Islamic republic shortly after
the triumph of the Islamic revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
One device, he said, was to replace former officials with
their own elements here in which they failed. The second one was
a military coup which was discovered and aborted, and the third
one was the imposition of a war on Iran with the involvement of
Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Tehran believed that the U.S. is now spearheading a worldwide
effort to further isolate the Islamic republic and to serve the
purpose military means may also be possibly explored.
</P>
<P>
Be prepared for possible warfare, the Iranian authorities have
raised the country's military budget about 40 percent in the new
fiscal year starting from March 21 over that of last year.
</P>
<P>
Some 25 billion rials (8.3 million U.S. dollars) have been
earmarked for upgrading the country's defense capacity, according
to local press reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
