<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
closed more than one percent higher today boosted by strength
across key industrials and resources.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said institutions returned to buying in the market, as
expectations of another interest rate cut to stimulate the economy
grew.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed up 29.2 points, or
1.21 percent, at 2442.4.
</P>
<P>
Broker Bill Richmond said the weak Australian dollar was a
factor in today's rise, but he believed, "the chances of a rate
cut in Australia are about 98 percent."
</P>
<P>
"I think the feeling is becoming stronger and stronger that we
may get a rate cut if inflation turns to deflation," Stuart Smith
from Lance Jones said.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index closed up 41.9 points at 3844.0,
while all resources index was 20 points firmer at 1361.3.
</P>
<P>
The banking index added 67.2 points to 4208.8, while the gold
index improved 26.6 points to 1582.8.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 389.20 million shares valued at 1.095
billion Australian dollars (848.6 million US dollars). 
</P>
