<HEADLINE> Floods Destroy 100 Farms in S. Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 18 (Xinhua)-- About 100 farms in the Lower
Shabelle Region of southern Somalia were destroyed yesterday by
floods from the Shabelle River.
</P>
<P>
Reports from the region said the floods crushed the flowering
farms of maize, sorghum and sesames at Bulo Marer and Jerow
villages 120 km south of here. The floods also destroyed a large
grazing land for animals.
</P>
<P>
The reports said people in Bulo Marer today began to push the
water aside with sand carried in buckets and wheelbarrows.
</P>
<P>
According to the elders of the Bulo Marer Village, they
tried to contact the relief agencies in the region but did not
get any answer.
</P>
<P>
The elders said they are appealing to the international aid
agencies elsewhere in the country to help them stop the water.
</P>
<P>
Similar floods hit some farming areas in the Middle Shabelle
Region last November when the Shabelle River crushed its
banks. enditem

