with N. F. Domashkevich, president of the State Control Commission
of Belarus here today.
</P>
<P>
Buhe, an ethnic Mongolian, is one of the 16 vice-Chairpersons
of the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The State Control Commission is the most powerful supervisory
body in Belarus.
</P>
<P>
In the Great Hall of the People, Buhe briefed Domashkevich and
his entourage on the system of supervision of government
officials in China.
</P>
<P>
He said that the supervisory system has been effective in
cracking down on corruption.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the two countries should conduct
more intensive exchanges between their governmental supervision
departments. They should learn from each other's experience so as
to better serve their countries' economic development, Buhe said.
</P>
<P>
Domashkevich said that this visit will help promote their work
at home through the exchanges with their Chinese counterparts.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the governmental supervision departments of the
two countries will increase their cooperation. 
</P>
