<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet OKs Budget for Fiscal Year 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet has endorsed a
preliminary fiscal budget of 1,008.08 billion baht (40.32 billion
U.S. dollars) for the fiscal year 1998, an increase of 83.08
billion baht (3.33 billion dollars) from the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Transport and Communications will receive a
budget of 102.34 billion baht (4.09 billion dollars), or an
increase of 21.46 percent from the fiscal year 1997, the highest
increase margin among the ministries, according to the Thai
Government House today.
</P>
<P>
The Education Ministry will receive a budget of 171.15 billion
baht (6.8 billion dollars), up 13.18 percent from the previous
fiscal year, ranking second.
</P>
<P>
The defense budget is set at 107.22 billion baht (4.29 billion
dollars), up 3.13 percent from the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
However, the Thai government slightly cut its budgets for the
Prime Minister's Office, the Finance Ministry, the Foreign
Ministry, and the Labor Ministry.
</P>
<P>
In terms of the shares of the budget among the ministries, the
Interior Ministry accounts for 17.9 percent, ranking first, while
the Education Ministry accounts for 17.0 percent ranking second,
followed by the Defense Ministry with 10.6 percent and the
Ministry of Transport and Communications with 10.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Foreign Ministry will take only a 0.4-percent share of
the budget for the fiscal year 1998, the lowest among the
ministries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
