<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Vice-Chairman Meets With Nepali Parliamentarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress Buhe met today
with a delegation from the Foreign Affairs and Human Rights
Committee of the Nepali parliament, led by Committee Chairman Jaya
Prakash Prasad Anand in Beijing's Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have a long history of good neighborly
relations, Buhe said, and bilateral relations have developed
steadily since the two countries set up diplomatic relations 41
years ago. There have been frequent exchange of visits by senior
leaders and growing contact between the two parliaments in the
past few years.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation for Nepal's sticking to the "one
China" policy in the Tibet and Taiwan issues and for supporting
China's stand on human rights, and said that Anand's visit will
further enhance friendly cooperative relations between the two
countries and the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Anand restated Nepal's stand on the "one China" policy, and
said that Nepal will not allow any anti-Chinese activities or
attempts to split the country. He said he believes that a stronger
and more prosperous China is in the interest not only of Nepal but
also of China's other neighbors.  
</P>
