<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The third round of political
consultations by senior officials of China and the Association of
the Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) ran from from April 17 to 18
at Huangshan Mountain in east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and Abdul Kadir
Mohamad, secretary-general of the Malaysian Foreign Ministry,
jointly presided over the two-day event, which was attended by
government representatives of Malaysia, Indonesia, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand, Brunnel, and Vietnam, and representatives from
the ASEAN secretariat.
</P>
