<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Population Growth Over One Percent Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China's population grew 10.42
people per thousand last year to 1,223.89 million, according to the
State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The figure does not include people in Taiwan, Hong Kong and
Macao regions.
</P>
<P>
The Tibet Autonomous Region led the country in population
growth, with 24.7 people per thousand. Shanghai, with a growth
rate of 5.6 per thousand, was at the bottom of the chart.
</P>
<P>
The survey indicated that population growth tends to slow down
in developed areas. Shanghai, Beijing, and Tianjin cities, and
Shandong, Zhejiang and Jiangsu provinces in east China; and
Heilongjiang, Jilin and Liaoning provinces in northeast China had
a population growth of less than 13 per thousand.
</P>
<P>
Regions were people minority groups are concentrated saw the
fastest population growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
