<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Computer Parts Sales in Macao Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The sales of computer parts have
soared over the past few years in Macao as the territory is being
computerized and more people opt to assemble computer themselves.
</P>
<P>
Local computer parts dealers said their turnover grew over 20
percent in 1996 from 1995, with the profit rate reaching as high
as 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
Macao has been becoming increasingly computerized over the past
several years. Companies and offices have widely used computers in
their daily operation, resulting in aa boom business for computer
dealers.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the demand for computer parts and accessories rose
 sharply, with deals in computer parts becoming much profitable
following fierce market competition in computer sales.
</P>
<P>
In addition, many people prefer to assemble a machine by
themselves.
</P>
<P>
Computer dealers believe that the market potential for computer
parts will remain large in the coming few years.
</P>
<P>
"The computer parts market is still at its start-up stage,"
said a dealer. "We are convinced that there is a bright future for
sales of computer accessories and parts."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
