<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Toughens Penalty on Solvent Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Thursday
approved a draft amendment act to prevent abuse of volatile
solvents and those dealers who sell volatile solvents to minors
will face tougher penalties.
</P>
<P>
Under the amendment act of the 1990 royal decree on prevention
of volatile solvent abuse, the penalties on the sellers of
volatile solvents to minors aged below 17 will be increased to a
maximum prison sentence of two years from one year previously.
</P>
<P>
The fine on the sellers will also double to a maximum of 20,000
baht (800 U.S. dollars), according to a press release from the
Thai Government House today.
</P>
<P>
Those dealers who provide volatile solvents to known addicts
will be subject to a prison sentence up to three years and a fine
up to 30,000 baht (1,200 dollars), the release said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
