<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- After numerous consultations, President Jacques Chirac
could make a decision next Thursday on whether to dissolve the
National Assembly (lower house of parliament) and hold early
legislative elections, possibly in early June, in order to ease
France's entry into the European Monetary Union.
</P>
<P>
-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin announced Thursday in
Baden-Baden, Germany, that Russia and NATO could sign a charter on
bilateral relations on May 27 in Paris, thus opening the way for
NATO expansion. But he again excluded the possibility of agreeing
to NATO's deploying arms and troops in its new members in central
and eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- French police have detained 133 Corsicans since January
1997, in a tightened crackdown on separatists on the island. The
number, higher than the 104 arrests made in the whole year of
1996, shows the determination of the government to fight
separatism. 
</P>
