<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CCB to Attract More Funds from Major Economic Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB)
will focus on large and medium-sized cities to attract more
deposits this year, the bank's president Wang Qishan said today.
</P>
<P>
"The large and medium-sized cities are a major source of cash
flow to commercial banks, and that is why the CCB will give
priority to the expansion of businesses in these cities," Wang
said in his speech to the bank's conference on attracting deposits.
</P>
<P>
The bank's total deposits reached 1.1018 trillion yuan last
year, up about 40 percent from 1995, which ranked CCB the second
among the five major Chinese commercial banks in terms of total
deposits and newly-added deposits.
</P>
<P>
Financial experts say that the competition among commercial
banks is becoming tough, with more Chinese turning their attention
from banks to stocks, bonds, insurance and other investment means
to save their money.
</P>
<P>
CCB will speed up the savings and withdrawal process at all of
its branch offices in each city, and will connect the large cities
with a computer network.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank has taken measures against the increasing
financial risks, by reforming its accounting and auditing system,
and regulating the power limits of its branch presidents.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
