<HEADLINE> EDS-more details added Chinese, Egyptian Leaders (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the past few years, Li said, bilateral economic and trade
relations have seen continuous and steady development through
joint efforts, and that bilateral trade volume has increased by a
large amount and bilateral cooperation has expanded. He noted that
there are broad prospects for expanded bilateral economic and
trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
With the development of the two economies, the two governments
should encourage enterprises to strengthen cooperation in the
industrial sector with an eye on the international market, to
raise bilateral economic and trade relations to a new level.
</P>
<P>
El-Ganzouri said that Egypt is concentrating on economic
development, and that his country attaches importance to
cooperation with China and hopes that this cooperation can produce
new results.
</P>
<P>
Both leaders agreed on exploring new means of bilateral
economic and trade cooperation and spoke about some projects.
</P>
<P>
El-Ganzouri briefed Li on recent developments in the Middle
East peace talks and his view on future developments.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the Middle East peace process has made some
progress since the Madrid peace conference, a result of joint
efforts by Arabs and Israel, with the support of the international
community.
</P>
<P>
In reiterating the "land for peace" principle as a means of
resolving the Mideast question, Li said that China hopes that the
Arab and Israeli sides can continue political negotiations with a
practical and flexible attitude with full implementation of
previous agreements to push the peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that China is against anything that would poison
the atmosphere of the peace talks and endanger the peace process.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Li and El-Ganzouri attended a signing ceremony
of three documents on bilateral cooperation in trade, the power
industry, and science and technology.
</P>
