<HEADLINE> TV Programs Trade Fair to be Held in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A national trade fair of
domestically-made TV programs will be held in the capital of east
China's Zhejiang Province this June.
</P>
<P>
The event, set for June 15-17, is based on the first national
fair of the kind held last year, according to the Ministry of
Broadcasting, Film and Television.
</P>
<P>
It will attract representatives of TV stations, cable TV
stations and film studios at or above the city or county level,
provincial level program suppliers, publishers of audio-video
products and some overseas guests.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature TV shows, special programs and cartoons
produced by domestic TV stations or other TV program producers,
and also TV shows that were jointly filmed by Chinese and foreign
producers and have been approved by the Ministry of Broadcasting,
Film and Television.
</P>
<P>
China now produces approximately 8,000 TV shows each year,
which have become the most popular programming among TV stations
at various levels, according to Ministry officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
