<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Solve Electricity Problem in Rural Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Power and Energy Ministry of
Sri Lanka is panning to give electricity to at least 20 villages
by the end of 1998 as the major fraction of the non-electrified
houses are in rural areas, according to electrical department
sources today.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that more than 15,000 villages out of a total
of 25,000 in the country remain without electricity.
</P>
<P>
In view of the innumerable direct and indirect benefits
received by the rural population through electrification, it is
essential to increase the level of electrification faster in order
to assist the economic and social development of the country, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
About 45 percent of the households in Sri Lanka have been
electrified up to now.  
</P>
</TEXT>
