<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Key Optical Cable Project Passes Appraisal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- A key state optical cable project
passed appraisal here today, expected to greatly improve telecom
capabilities in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The 1,708-km-long project starts from Beijing and extends to
three provinces, including Hebei, Shanxi and Shaanxi, linking up
13 prefectures and 28 counties.
</P>
<P>
Designated as one of the key state optic cable telecom trunks,
it will be hooked up with those cables laid in the northeast,
north, northwest and east parts of China, forming China's
nationwide optic cable telecom networks.
</P>
<P>
Sources from China's Ministry of Post and Telecommunications
said that the new project initially can provide 20,000 digital
telecom lines.
</P>
<P>
The project, at the cost of 310 million yuan, used loans
provided by Asia Development Bank. All optic cable and other
equipment was purchased through open bidding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
