<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yinchuan Implements "Adequate Housing" Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Since 1995, about 2,000
low-income families in Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous region, have fulfilled their dream of
owning their own home.
</P>
<P>
An official with the municipal government said that the
"Adequate Housing" program in effect since the end of 1994 has
led to the completion of 102,000 square meters of housing in
Yinchuan.
</P>
<P>
Over the next six years, the city plans to invest 468 million
yuan (about 55.7 million US dollars) in constructing 600,000
square meters of houses.
</P>
<P>
The housing plan is based on the buying capacity of ordinary
citizens, the official said. Among the 59 cities participating in
the program, Yinchuan reports the lowest housing cost -- about
700-750 yuan per square meter.
</P>
<P>
Yinchuan government has established a quality-control system to
supervise construction, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
