<HEADLINE> Auctioning Off Name of Inner Mongolia's First Overpass </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Hohhot, capital of north China's
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, will hold a nationwide auction
for the right to name its first overpass and to use it for
advertising purposes.
</P>
<P>
The advertising right will be for 50 years, which, experts
believe, will be worth more than 200 million yuan, because of its
location in the center of Hohhot's city proper, a busy commercial
area.
</P>
<P>
The overpass is being built to commemorate the 50th anniversary
of the founding of the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, and
construction will soon be completed, Guangming Daily reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the largest auction so far in Inner Mongolia of
intangible state-owned property.  
</P>
</TEXT>
