<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Sees Flourishing Bamboo Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has made significant profits in the bamboo processing industry and
its bamboo-made products sell widely in the world market.
</P>
<P>
"Our products have exported to more than ten countries and
regions, such as the United States, Japan, and some European
countries," said Zhang Ronggen, a 40-year-old farmer.
</P>
<P>
He opened a bamboo processing factory in 1992. Last year, a
Taiwan businessman invested 200,000 US dollars helping Zhang with
the renewal of equipment.
</P>
<P>
The province now has nearly 630,000 hectares of bamboo forest,
which ranks fourth in the country. More than 2,000 factories have
been set up to process bamboo products, such as carvings,
decorations, and furniture.
</P>
<P>
The output value of the bamboo processing industry in Zhejiang
reached nearly 422 million US dollars last year, which included 80
million US dollars for exported products, according to a
provincial official.
</P>
<P>
The Anji County, known as the "sea of bamboo" in northern
Zhejiang, developed a bamboo-made floor last year, which was
hailed by consumers for its high quality and low price.  
</P>
</TEXT>
