<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Record Shattered in Short-Course Heats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 18 (Xinhua) -- German Sandra Voelker broke her
own European record in the women's 50 meters freestyle heats at
the World Short-Course Championships in Gothenburg on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Voelker swam home in 24.62 seconds, chopping off 0.05 seconds
from the mark set at the European Championships on December 14,
1996.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Le Jingyi of China finished second in the
heat and third overall in 25.05, behind American Jenny Thompson
who won her heat in 25.01, the second-fastest prior to the
evening's final.
</P>
<P>
Le, third-placer in her 100 freestyle defence on Thursday,
holds the current world record of 24.23 set at the inaugural World
Short-Course Championships in Palma de Mallorca in December 1993.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese woman won both the 50 and 100 freestyles at the
1993 and 1995 editions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
