<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rong Yiren Meets Latin American Parliament President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Rong Yiren
today expressed the hope that the National People's Congress (NPC)
will become an observer of the Latin American Parliament in the
near future.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with Juan Adolfo Singer, president of the Latin
American Parliament, at the Great Hall of the People here this
morning, Rong said China and Latin American countries are
developing countries and they share many common viewpoints on
major international issues.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Latin American Parliament is an important and
influential international organization, he said the NPC attaches
great importance to furthering the relationship between the two.
</P>
<P>
Last year, he said, the NPC formally applied to become an
observer of the parliament. Rong thanked the parliamentary members
of some Latin American countries for their positive efforts to
this end.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the NPC will become an observer of the Latin
American Parliament at an early date," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rong noted that the Taiwan authorities have been working
worldwide in an attempt to trick their way into the Latin American
Parliament and sabotage the friendly ties and cooperation between
the NPC and the parliament.
</P>
<P>
Their political intention is to create "two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan," which absolutely cannot be accepted by the
Chinese People, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Rong extended his warm welcome to Singer
and his party and expressed the belief that their visit will help
deepen mutual understanding and cooperation between the NPC and
the Latin American Parliament.
</P>
<P>
He said that the NPC has maintained close contact and good
cooperation with most of the member states of the Latin American
Parliament.
</P>
<P>
Rong said he hopes that their exchanges will develop so as to
promote mutually beneficial cooperation between China and Latin
American Countries in the fields of politics, economy, trade,
culture, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Singer said the Latin American countries' cooperation with
China will be beneficial to the entire world.
</P>
<P>
The Latin American countries place great importance on
developing their ties with China. Therefore, the Latin American
Parliament will establish a long and friendly relationship with
China's NPC, he said.
</P>
<P>
Singer said the issue of China's application to be an observer
of the Latin American Parliament will be settled successfully, and
the parliament will not discuss the issue concerning the
development of its relationship with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Rong also briefed the visitors on China's economic growth.
</P>
</TEXT>
