<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 players, including
college seniors, veterans with prior professional experience and
international players, will attend the inaugural WNBA Pre-Draft
Camp from April 19-22 at Disney's Wide World of Sports Complex in
Orlando, Florida.
</P>
<P>
Players physical examinations will be conducted by
league-appointed medical personnel on Saturday, April 19 at the
Disney Institute. The Pre-Draft Camp begins on Sunday, April 20
at the Disney Fieldhouse with players participating in drills and
games. The Pre-Draft camp will run through Tuesday, April 22.
</P>
<P>
All participants in the WNBA Pre-Draft Camp are eligible for
the WNBA Draft on April 28. Each team currently has four palyers
on its roster and will make four selections during the WNBA Draft
to increase its eight players. Local tryouts will be conducted in
mid-May to complete each team's roster, which will include 10
active players and two developmental players.
</P>
<P>
The WNBA will begin play on June 21. Each team will play a
28-game regular season, and four teams will qualify for the WNBA
Playoffs, which will include two semifinal games on August 28 and
the championship game on August 30. 
