<HEADLINE> Beijing's Foreign Trade for First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital had 703
million US dollars worth of imports and exports in the first
quarter of this year, recent statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's foreign trade volume has gone up slightly this year,
compared with the continued downturn in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Imports accounted for 234 million dollars, down 28.4 percent
from the same period of 1996, and exports for 470 million dollars,
a rise of 3.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Exports from overseas-funded enterprises kept up the increase,
rising 51.3 percent to 180 million US dollars worth. Processed
exports accounted for 55.9 percent of the total, contributing
greatly to the increase in exports from overseas-funded
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The city's overseas-funded enterprises mainly export machinery,
electronics products, and clothing. Major exports from state-owned
enterprises are clothing, iron and steel, textiles, and cotton.
</P>
<P>
The city exports to more than 130 countries and regions. This
year, Beijing's exports are expected to be worth 2.3 billion US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
