<HEADLINE> Krajicek Reaches Final Four in Japan Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek
of the Netherlands beat David Prinosil of Germany on Friday to
reach the semi-finals in the Japan Open here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The top seed Krajicek, ranked seventh in the world, never faced
serious challenge from the 48th-ranked Prinosil, winning both sets
6-4, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals on Saturday, Krajicek will take on the
winner of an all-Australian affair between Patrick Rafter and Todd
Woodbridge.
</P>
<P>
Lionel Roux of France, who eliminated three-time Wimbledon
champion Boris Becker of Germany on Thursday, moved another step
forward by beating seventh-seeded Martin Damm of the Czech
Republic 6-3, 6-1 in the quarter finals.
</P>
<P>
He plays the winner of the quarter final between fifth seed
Thomas Johansson of Sweden and Australian Mark Woodforde.
</P>
<P>
In the women's field, 1995 champion Amy Frazier of the United
States secured a final berth for a fourth consecutive year when
she overwhelmed Annabel Ellwood of Australia 6-2, 6-3. 
</P>
