<DOCNO> XIE19970418.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Key Dam Project Sprints to the Finish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Over 10,000 Chinese and foreign
workers are working day and night at the Xiaolangdi Dam Project,
the largest of its kind on the Yellow River, to make sure it will
be dammed as scheduled on October 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
More than 11 million cubic meters of earth and stone have been
poured into the river from both sides to form a 200-meter-high dam
with a gap left for damming.
</P>
<P>
Work on the intake tower, the most difficult part of the
project, has been completed. The three tunnel intakes, each with a
length of 1,100 meters and a diameter of 14.5 meters have been
constructed. Workers are building an inner lining with bricks.
</P>
<P>
Work on a pool to reduce the impulsive force of flood at the
outlet of the three tunnel intakes has been half completed. Over
85 percent of the earthwork for the power house has been done.
</P>
<P>
More than 7,000 households with a population of 20,000 living
in the dam area have moved to new villages.
</P>
<P>
Cao Zhengqi, chief engineer in charge of the Xiaolangdi
project, said the whole project is going on smoothly and the
quality is up to set standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
