<HEADLINE> Ballistic Missile Successfully Launched in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Strategic Rocket
Troops successfully launched a multi-headed PC-20 intercontinental
ballistic missile today, military sources said.
</P>
<P>
All its 10 payloads hit their targets in the designated area of
the Kamchatka Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The missile was launched at 15:30 (local time) at the Paikonur
testing site in Kazakhstan that has been rented by Russia for 20 years.
</P>
<P>
It is Russia's first training launch of an intercontinental
ballistic missile this year.
</P>
<P>
Igor Sergeyev, strategic rocket troops commander in charge of
the project, said the launch was to check the missile's function.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the PC-20 missile, in service for 20 years
already, would possiblely have its service period extended.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Strategic Rocket Troops have conducted 25
successful launches of PC-20 in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
