<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Car Theft Serious in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Car stealing has became a
serious problem in Hungary in recent years, local newspapers
said here today.
</P>
<P>
About 16,000 cars were stolen last year, 3,000 more than in
1995 and car theft resulted in a loss of 16 billion forint to the
country.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the number of stolen cars in the whole of Europe
doubled, but the number in Hungary increased 20 times.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian authorities are taking measures to combat the
crime, though only 6 percent of car thefts are
solved at present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
