<HEADLINE> Landslide Hits Bulgarian Seaside </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A big landslide near the Bulgarian
coastal city of Varna has destroyed houses and installations for
tourists, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
This was the second and the biggest landslide to occur near
Varna this year.
</P>
<P>
The reports said the foundations of some stretches of the road
between Varna and "Golden Beach" sank five meters, and the
subsidences in some areas was still going on.
</P>
<P>
About 50 buildings were leveled and a number of
newly-established hotels were in danger of caving in.
</P>
<P>
Water and power supplies as well as communications in the Varna
area were totally cut.
</P>
<P>
The local authorities ordered the suspension of all
construction projects in the area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
