<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Ready to Provide Alba Troops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria is ready to send troops to
join the Italian-led multinational force which has started "Alba"
operations in Albania, the Bulgarian Foreign Ministry said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by a Bulgarian official committee which
is responsible for promoting Bulgarian membership of NATO. It was
conveyed by the first vice foreign minister of Bulgaria, Valentin
Dobrev, to the Italian ambassador in Sofia.
</P>
<P>
The committee urged the general headquarters of the Bulgarian
army to send a unit of limited numbers to participate in the Alba
operations in Albania.
</P>
<P>
However, the exact number of Bulgarian soldiers joining the
multinational force was not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The committee also decided to make financial preparations for
Bulgaria's joining NATO.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council passed a resolution on
March 25 authorizing the dispatch of a 6,000-member, Italian-led
multinational force for three months to protect relief operations
in chaos-torn Albania.
</P>
<P>
Besides Italy, France, Spain, Greece, Turkey, Austria, Denmark
and Romania have sent soldiers to Albania.  
</P>
</TEXT>
