<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Party Leader Describes China Impressions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 17 (Xinhua) -- China attaches importance to
learning from the capitalist world whatever can accelerate its
scientific progress, says Honorary Chairman of the Democratic
Socialist Party Hans Modrow.
</P>
<P>
Modrow was talking to a German newspaper about his impressions
of China during his visit between April 5 and 13.
</P>
<P>
China implements a policy of reform and opening up and builds
socialism with Chinese characteristics, he told the Nenes
Dentschland newspaper on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said China has come to know the problems emerging during the
process of reform and opening up, such as those existing in
state-owned enterprises, and the problems of social welfare.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leaders were determined to carry out the behests of
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping, whose death did not mean an
interruption in the implementation of the policy he inaugurated,
said Modrow, who visited China in 1959 and again in 1992.
</P>
<P>
On the human rights issue, Modrow said: "I think that so long
as people have food, housing and work in a country with a
1.2-billion population, the basic human rights there are
guaranteed."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese leaders are willing to conduct dialogue on the
human rights issue," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added, "No problem can be solved by means of sheer
confrontation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
