<HEADLINE> More Training for Sri Lanka's Teachers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka has launched a program
to provide further training for trained teachers every five years
commencing from this year, Education Ministry sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The new program is designed to educate teachers on the latest
developments in the education system including the revised
syllabuses and new teaching methods.
</P>
<P>
The program was initiated by the Education Ministry's special
unit responsible for the professional advancement of those
employed in the education service, the sources stated.
</P>
<P>
The unit has already started a number of activities countrywide
including a series of seminars for teachers and officials during
the last few months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
