<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Police Arrests Drug, Arms Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Italian police arrested 25 drug and
arms traffickers in the two-day action called "Querce" in Perugia,
in southern Italy.
</P>
<P>
In the action, police also confiscated four kilograms of
cocaine, weapons and a large amount of ammunitions.
</P>
<P>
Police has investigated the criminal group for 20 months which
planned to ship weapons, including machine guns, from Bosnia to
Italy and resell them for profit. 
</P>
