<HEADLINE> Peasants Urged to Boost Farm Production in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar Minister for Agriculture
and Irrigation Lieutenant-General Myint Aung today urged peasants
in the country to double their efforts to boost farm production
in the monsoon cultivation season for 1997-98.
</P>
<P>
In his message to the peasants on the occasion of Myanmar New
Year, Myint Aung disclosed that Myanmar's agricultural production
in the 1996-97 fiscal year ended March 31 has increased by 3.7 per
cent.
</P>
<P>
To enhance agricultural production, he said, the government is
providing assistance to peasants in boosting per-hectare yield and
multiple cropping and extending cultivated area.
</P>
<P>
In order to make more water available, he added, altogether 76
dams have been built since 1988, irrigating 486,000 hectares of
farmland.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar's paddy output in the
1995-96 fiscal year was recorded at 19 million tons, while its
rice export was at 353,100 tons.
</P>
<P>
The annual growth rate of Myanmar's agriculture in the last
four fiscal years from 1992-93 to 1995-96 stood at 8.8 percent and
is targeted at 5.4 per cent in the next five fiscal years from
1996-97 to 2000-2001.  
</P>
</TEXT>
