<HEADLINE> Unseasonal Cold Blast Hits Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCKAREST, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A sudden cold spell in Romania
has brought on snow and strong winds in many ports of Romania
recently, with some farm land and electricity services out of
action.
</P>
<P>
A lot of farm land was flooded in the southern part of the
country, where there was heavy rain for more than 10 consecutive
days.
</P>
<P>
The cold current which came in from the north brought snow
which fell 30 to 40 centimeters thick in central and eastern
Romania.
</P>
<P>
Strong winds snapped electric wires in more than 100 townships
in the south, though there was little snow there.
</P>
<P>
Experts predicted that the weather could not improve until the
end of April.
</P>
<P>
A warm winter last year was seen by experts as the cause of the
abnormal spring weather there and other parts of southern
Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
