<HEADLINE> China to Launch New Prices Checks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China will launch a series of
large scale prices checks in key sectors such as railway transport
and agricultural products this year, according to a Beijing-based
newspaper recently.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year, China's price checking and
administrative departments will check the fees charged by the
departments in charge of construction, land-use, social security,
and labor forces, Monday's Township Enterprises Daily said.
</P>
<P>
The illegal fee charging actions, such as raising charging
standards and extending the charging range in these sectors will
be stopped and punished, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
The overcharging on housing projects will be paid special
attention.
</P>
<P>
Overcharging on services in the railway transport sector has
been a big problem for several years in the country, the price
administrative departments noted, saying they will redouble their
efforts to check the transport fee and major service fee charged
on trains.
</P>
<P>
Through checks, prices of agricultural means of production,
such as chemical fertilizers and pesticides, will be kept
reasonably low for farmers to protect their initiative for
agricultural production, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The high prices for medicines and commission for medical
personnel will also be curbed during two large-scale checks this
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
