<HEADLINE> BID To Choose ALCA Seat City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The cities that intend to
become the seat of future negotiations for the creation of the
Americas Free Trade Area (ALCA) must file their bids before April
30.
</P>
<P>
The proposed city will be selected by the Interamerican
Development Bank (BID), said Jose Botafogo Gonzalves,
undersecretary for economic affairs in the Brazilian Foreign
Relations Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during the meeting of 32 commerce
vice ministers of the Americas which concluded today in Rio de
Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
So far five cities have shown interests being among the
contenders in the selection process: Rio de Janeiro in Brazil,
Santafe de Bogota in Colombia, and the capitals of Panama, Mexico,
and Argentine, said Botafogo.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-four nations of the American continent committed
themselves in December, 1995, to establishing the ALCA, starting
in 2005. 
