<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Experts Warn of Surplus Motorcycle Production Capacity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics show that
China's motorcycle production capacity reached 14.89 million by
1995, 50 percent higher than the planned capacity for the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
The statistics from the State Statistics Bureau (SSB) said that
there are still 22 motorcycle projects under construction at
present, with expected production capacity of 3.83 million
motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
Experts thus warned firms to keep sober minded and stop
investing in motorcycle production.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, a lot of local governments set the
sector as the backbone and new driving force for their economic
development, expecting bumper profits.
</P>
<P>
Their overinput brought the number of motorcycle factories to
139 in 1996 from about 20.
</P>
<P>
In the January-August period in 1996, the business volume in
this sector decreased by 31.6 percent over the same period the
previous year, while their taxes and profits dropped by 87.3
percent. Illegal competition also occured on the market.
</P>
<P>
The SSB said that most of the current motorcycle projects under
construction are small-scale ones whose annual production capacity
would be lower than 200,000 motorcycles. The low level techniques
will also impact the market prospects for these firms.
</P>
<P>
Another survey by the SSB show that in 1996, every 100 urban
households have six motorcycles. In 1993, the figure was 3.5.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
