<HEADLINE> Thompson Wins Women's 100m Freestyle Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Jenny Thompson beat Atlanta
Olympic gold medalist Le Jingyi of China to bring the United
States its first title of the World Short-Course Championships in
the women's 100 meters freestyle in Gothenburg, Sweden, on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Sandra Voelker, the European short-course champion
and silver medallist behind Le at Atlanta Olympics, went through
the 50-meter mark in 25.23 seconds, inside Le's world record
schedule.
</P>
<P>
But she could not quite sustain the pace and Thompson, a relay
gold medallist at the last two Olympics, surged through to win by
just 0.04 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Thompson, 100 freestyle silver medallist at the 1992 Olympics,
clocked 53.46 seconds to edge out Voelker.
</P>
<P>
Le, who completed the golden doubles in the 50 and 100
freestyles at the last two World Short-Course Championships, had
to settle for a bronze in 53.72. 
