<HEADLINE> China on Guard Against Medfly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese inspection officials are
urging nationwide efforts to halt the entry of a bee-like insect
called the Mediterranean Fruit Fly into the country, as it may
cause mammoth economic losses for fruit growers, "China Daily"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Inspection officials of the Tianjin Branch of the China
Administration of Animal and Plant Quarantine (CAAPQ) confiscated
five oranges carried in by a Belarusan passenger from Minsk at
Tianjin's international airport last month.
</P>
<P>
Five Medflies were found inside the oranges, the official said.
</P>
<P>
China previously found Medflies at least six times at its
customs locations in southern areas over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
CAAPQ is making efforts to strengthen its inspections across
the country with relevant official departments and expects much
co-operation from traders and passengers who declare their
agricultural products for quarantine inspection.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the Medfly has already spread to more than 80
countries and regions in the world, although it is relatively new
to China.
</P>
<P>
The Medfly eats more than 250 kinds of fruits and vegetables. A
pair of male and female Medflies can reproduce 200 million eggs
within 60 days.
</P>
<P>
The world's scientists have not yet found an effective way to
kill the Medfly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970418.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FIVB Introduces Experimental Rules in Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, April 17 (Xinhua) -- To cope with the nagging issue
of prolonged volleyball competitions, FIVB decided on Thursday to
introduce two experimental rules in the world-class competitions.
</P>
<P>
As a rule, each set will be restricted within 25 minutes with
an exception for the deciding set that bears no timing limit, FIVB
president Ruben Acosta said at the 50th anniversary of the
International Volleyball Federation.
</P>
<P>
And a set game system will be applied with rally point to the
best of three sets, each set in two games of 21 points with
eventual sudden death in case.
</P>
<P>
Of a tie, the current two-point system will be carried out,
FIVB said.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the sport's world governing body said a new ball with
one centimeter longer in diameter will also be introduced into the
competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
