<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Frolander Wins 100m Butterfly Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Swede Lars Frolander captured
the first title of the world short-course swimming championships
for hosts Sweden by winning men's 100 meters butterfly in
Gothenburg, Sweden, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Frolander touched home in 51.95 seconds, with Australians Geoff
Huegill taking the silver in 51.99 and Michael Klim at third in
52.02.
</P>
<P>
Frolander, the fastest qualifier, trailed sixth of the eight
finalists at the halfway point of the race.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Denis Pankratov of Russia failed to qualify
for the final, having finished a well-beaten fifth in his morning
heat and 11th overall.
</P>
<P>
Pankratov's heat time of 53.48 seconds was way outside his
51.78 world short-course record set in Paris at a World Cup meet
in February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
