<HEADLINE> Liu Wins Women's 200m Butterfly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Liu Limin claimed the gold in
the women's 200 meters butterfly event at the world short-course
swimming championships in Gothenburg, Sweden, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This is the third butterfly gold she won in three world
short-course championships.
</P>
<P>
American Misty Hyman and Japan's Hitomi Kashima led the Olympic
silver medalist until the eighth and final length when Liu made a
storming surge to clock two minutes 7.20 seconds for the gold.
</P>
<P>
Liu also won the event at the inaugural world short-course
championships in Palma de Mallorca and took the 100m event at the
1995 edition in Rio de Janeiro.
</P>
<P>
Kashima took the silver in 2:07.34 and Hyman the bronze in
2:07.54, ahead of China's Qu Yun in 2:08.74. 
</P>
