<HEADLINE> Chinese President Expresses Sympathy Over Mina Fire Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin has
expressed sympathy to King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz of Saudi Arabia
over the victims of a fire that swept through the tents of Muslim
pilgrims near Mecca on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"I feel greatly grieved for the pilgrim victims of, and the
losses caused by, a big fire in Mina, Mecca," Jiang said in a
message of sympathy, dated April 17, to King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of the Chinese people and in my own name, I express
my heartfelt sympathy to Your Majesty, the Saudi government and
the people, and my sincere condolences to the relatives of the
victims of the accident," he said.
</P>
