<HEADLINE> Cuban-French Food Bakery in Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Cuban President Fidel Castro
attended the inauguration ceremony today of the Francuba bakery
and candy manufacturing factory, a Cuban-French joint enterprise.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban president stressed that this is a direct result of
French investment in Cuba, and warned Francuba executives that
they must maintain their standards of quality to face any
competition.
</P>
<P>
Francuba vice-president Michel Villand, and the firm lawyer,
Stepahn Boujnah, praised the investors for their courage to face
the pressures exerted by the United States through the
Helms-Burton law. The law discourages investments and trade with
Cuba.
</P>
<P>
The factory is designed to produce 2.5 tons of French-type
bread every day. enditem


