<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- Canada completed the round robin
play with three wins on Thursday as both men and women topped
their standings and qualified for the semi-finals at the World
Curling Championships in Bern, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian women defeated Sweden 12-4 in seven ends in the
morning before downing Denmark 9-3 to finish with an 8-1 record.
</P>
