<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Tertiary Industry on High Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- China invested 34.6 billion yuan
in the tertiary industry in the first two months of this year, up
19.9 percent from the same period of 1996, said the latest
statistics released by the State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the January-February period, China poured 10.23 billion yuan
into the fixed assets of the transportation and postal and telecom
services, an increase of 20.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's sectors of commerce, food service, materials
supply, marketing, and warehousing received a combined investment
of 1.16 billion yuan, up 6.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The investment in the real estate management and public,
residential and consultancy services amounted to 16.92 billion
yuan, up 17.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
That in the banking and insurance businesses was 343 million
yuan, up 7.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970418.0255 </DOCNO>
