<HEADLINE> China's Retail Sales Went Upward in January, February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 18 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from the
State Statistical Bureau show that China's retail sales of social
consumer goods reached 450.2 billion yuan during the first two
months of this year, up 16.1 percent from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The top three were the provinces of Guangdong, Jiangsu and
Shandong.
</P>
<P>
The retail sales of Guangdong was 50.4 billion yuan, up 16.8
percent from the correspondent period of last year.
</P>
<P>
That of Jiangsu was 37.2 billion yuan, up 13.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Shandong registered retail sales of 31.9 billion yuan, up 18.3
percent. 
