<HEADLINE> World Bank Finances Public Management Project in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 17 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today approved
a 44 million U.S. dollar credit for a public sector management
project in support of the Kyrgyz government's economic reform
program.
</P>
<P>
The project is designed to help enhance economic growth and
improve living standards by reducing the fiscal deficit and
strengthening the management of public sector resources.
</P>
<P>
The credit, which will be channeled by the International
Development Association (IDA), the concessionary lending arm of
the World Bank, will be disbursed in two equal tranches.
</P>
<P>
The Kyrgyz Republic joined the World Bank and the IDA in
September 1992. The IDA credits to the country total some 358
million dollars equivalent for 12 projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
