<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Explosion Kills Five, Injures 18 in B.C., Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 17 (Xinhua) -- A powerful explosion has killed
five and injured 18 in the Canadian province of British Columbia
(B.C.), said reports today.
</P>
<P>
The explosion leveled a small commercial building late
Wednesday afternoon in Quesnel, a community about 400 kilometers
north of Vancouver.
</P>
<P>
Four bodies were pulled out from the fiery debris, and a fifth
person was confirmed dead today, police said.
</P>
<P>
A natural gas leak is the suspect of the explosion, which
destroyed a thrift shop and sports card shop and left people
trapped in debris, screaming for help.
</P>
<P>
"The front of the building was blown across the street and the
other walls were blown out. One of the cars across the street was
flipped," one witness was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which was felt kilometers away, left a crater where
the building once stood, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
